sub_unit.note: The returns from Greenville were rejected, the transcript not having been certified by the county clerk.

sub_unit.name: Bengal
sub_unit.note: The town's original name was Orange, formed April 3, 1807 but was changed to Bengal April 6, 1808, and finally to Vienna April 12, 1816, only a month before the election. Reports of the election results still listed it as Bengal.
